These supplement I have been taking on and off which genuinely helped me so much achieving a good skin health! 

1. Zitcare: I took specially during my acne breakout time! I was another medication also hence used to take one tab in a day and I took it around 2 months.

2. Cutilift: this has omega 3 fatty acid so you can take it daily bed time till you want! Take a break if you feel so!

3. Havglo: take for around 2-3 months to see visible difference!

4. Nutrova collagen: take one sachet daily for best results! I take for 2-3 months then break for a month or so and get back to it again.

Just an advice: you need to be very regular with their intake for at least 2-3 months to have the best results and with this your regular skin care should be continued.

Disclaimer: These supplements are based on personal experience and should be taken after getting prescribed by your doctor, don’t try to consume in any known case of allergy and kidney disease.

If you thought those skin-coloured small bumps on your forehead and chin were harmless, I have some news for you. ⬆️

These are comedian acne and can progress into inflammatory acne if you don’t take care of them. 

They occur due to increased sebum production and we all know how frequent that is during summer season. 

@Acnestar is celebrating Acne awareness month and I am glad to be apart of their campaign to spread awareness on various types of acne we all come across. I hope you watch this video and learn to take care of those little bumps that are sure to cause bumps in your summer skincare journey.

#AcneAnswersByAcnestar #AcneAwarenessMonth
 #SkinCareRoutine #ForeheadAcne #AcneStar #ComedonalAcne #indianskintips

These all products work great specially during this season.

1. Sebamed foaming face wash: great for oily to combination skin type. You can use it twice a day.

2. Rivela vitamin C serum: use after cleansing in day time and top it up with moisturiser and sunscreen. Works great to fight radical damage to skin and brightens skin and have anti aging benefits also.

3. Acne UV sunscreen: its matt sunscreen hence great for this season. Use it daily.

4. Wishcare under arm roll on: works great for underarm odour and darkness. Use it 1-2 times in a day daily.

5. Tyrodin lotion: one of my go to for body tanning, uneven skin ton or to brighten skin tone. Use it 1-2 times in a day.

This video is for informative purpose and I would insist you all to always Use these products under Doctor’s guidance only!
